text.section:
The appointing authority shall:
based on appropriate standards, place the candidates within the following categories:
best qualified;
better qualified;
qualified;
unsatisfactory;
certified by the Division of Rehabilitation Services;
eligible for reinstatement after layoff or after a separation under § 11-302 of this article;
eligible for reinstatement; or
eligible for transfer; and
place the candidates on a list of eligible candidates by category in random order within the category except for candidates eligible for reinstatement after layoff or separation under § 11-302 of this article who shall be placed in that category in seniority point order.
